==English==

===Etymology===
French [[appartement]]; compare with Italian [[appartamento]], from [[appartare]] to separate, set apart; all from Latin [[ad]] + [[pars]], [[partis]], [[part]].  See [[Apart]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈpɑɹt.mɛnt/

===Noun===
'''apartment'''  (''plural:'' '''[[apartments]]''')
# A room in a building; a division in a house, separated from others by partitions.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[asunto#Finnish|asunto]]
*French: [[appartement]] {{m}}
*German: [[Wohnung]] {{f}}
*Italian: [[appartamento]] {{m}}
*Swedish: [[lägenhet]]

====Synonyms====
[[flat]] (British), [[unit]], compare with [[condominium]]

